OL,3,CThree caskets and a smashed ring: The
OL,4,Cancient traditions after the Pope's
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,FFollowing the death of a pope and the
OL,8,Fcompletion of official rites, the
OL,9,FCatholic Church enters a nine-day
OL,10,Fperiod of mourning known as the
OL,11,Fnovemdiales.
OL,13,FDuring this time, the faithful are
OL,14,Finvited to pay their respects, and the
OL,15,Fpope's body lies in state for public
OL,16,Fviewing.
OL,18,FTraditionally, deceased pontiffs were
OL,19,Fburied in three nested coffins -
OL,20,Fcypress, lead, and oak - reflecting
OL,21,Flayers of symbolism and security.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
