OL,3,CThree caskets and a smashed ring: The
OL,4,Cancient traditions after the Pope's
OL,5,Cdeath
OL,7,FHowever, in recent years, this ritual
OL,8,Fhas been simplified. The pope is now
OL,9,Fplaced in a wooden coffin lined with
OL,10,Fzinc.
OL,12,FThe pope is dressed in red liturgical
OL,13,Fvestments, his mitre - the traditional
OL,14,Fheaddress of bishops - and the pallium
OL,15,Fwoolen stole, a type of scarf.
OL,17,FThe Pasqual candle, a large, decorated
OL,18,Fcandle used at Easter, is placed
OL,19,Fnearby.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/16
